## Use Cases

**API documentation** - TSDoc comments converted to mdz at build time, rendered with auto-linking at runtime

**Documentation pages** - manual docs written in mdz (like this file)

**Component descriptions** - props and behavior with auto-linked code identifiers

**Inline help text** - lightweight formatting without full markdown complexity

## Implementation

**Parser** - `mdz.ts` - single-pass character-code-based lexer/parser

**Renderer** - `Mdz.svelte` - component wrapper for parsing and rendering

**Context** - `mdz_components_context` and `mdz_elements_context` for opt-in components/elements

**Integration** - `tsdoc_helpers.ts` converts TSDoc to mdz at build time

## Status

mdz is an **early proof of concept** with comprehensive test coverage but limited feature set. Lists and blockquotes are next. The API and syntax may change as we learn from real-world usage.

**Current version:** Fuz v0.150.0
